The intellectual property underlying "The Sound of Silence" encompasses both the underlying musical composition (the words and music) and the specific sound recordings.
	•	Composition and Lyrics: Written entirely by Paul Simon. The music publishing rights—which govern the composition and lyrics—were historically administered under Paul Simon Music and Eclectic Music. In April 2021, Paul Simon sold his entire music publishing catalog to Sony Music Publishing, which now acts as the permanent custodian and administrator of the song's copyright. 
	•	Sound Recordings (Master Rights): The original acoustic version (1964) and the definitive electronic overdubbed single version (1965) were recorded for and released by Columbia Records. These master recording rights are owned by Sony Music Entertainment. 
	•	Recording Royalty Streams: While Sony retains ownership of the master recordings, Paul Simon sold his personal artist royalty income stream and neighboring rights income stream for Simon & Garfunkel recordings to BMG in June 2023. 
